title: Grateful Dead Live at Providence Civic Center on 1979-01-18
lineage: DAT > CDR > EAC(secure) > Cool Edit > CDWAV > mkwact > SHN
description: Promised Land, They Love Each Other, Mama Tried-> Mexicali Blues, Friend Of The Devil, Cassidy, Jack A Roe, Looks Like Rain, Ramble On Rose, Minglewood Blues, Deal I Need A Miracle-> Bertha-> Good Lovin', From The Heart Of Me, Ship of Fools, He's Gone-> Truckin'-> The Other One-> Wharf Rat-> Around & Around, E: U.S. Blues

reviews.review_text: why no reviews? Why has no one reviewed this?  It may not be the all time best, but o.k...... a 4

pretty good A nice audience recording, sounds like a soundboard at times.  Weir seems up in the mix, you can hear his chops and fills distinctly.  Garcia's voice is good, his playing quite fast, like most of the rest of this January run.  Not sure what the highlights here are (yet)....the other concerts in this stretch seem more interesting.

Why no drums this night? I haven't listened yet, but it looks like no drums. Anyone know why??

Second, it is really irritating to hear people complain that they "toured their as* off" and because of that the Dead should give them all recordings for free forever. 

I saw 200+ shows, but that was 15-30 years ago. The Dead don't owe anyone anything. Maybe if some of these peole had taken a bath more than once a month they might deserve it, but there were plenty of nights I had to move from good seats because the people next to me stunk so bad! Either that or they sung at the top of their lungs and thats all I could hear.
